olive oil
1 Avocado
2 Radish
1 sprig Spring Onion
1 Orange
1 packet Halloumi
1 tsp honey
1 packet balsamic glaze
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet Slivered Almonds
1 packet mint

• Slice avocado in half, scoop out flesh and thinly slice.
• Thinly slice radish and spring onion.
• Peel and thinly slice orange into wedges.
• Cut flavoured halloumi into 1cm slices.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook halloumi until golden brown, 1-2 minutes each side.
• Remove pan from heat, then add the honey and turn to coat. Transfer to a plate.

• In a medium bowl, combine balsamic glaze, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper.
• To the bowl, add orange, radish, spring onion and mixed salad leaves. Toss to combine.

• Divide orange and radish salad between plates.
• Top with avocado and glazed halloumi.
• Sprinkle over slivered almonds.
• Tear over mint to serve. Enjoy!